The paper deals with complexity and algorithmic aspects of matrix completion, which are central topics in computational complexity theory. The use of determinantal complexity and explicit multilinear polynomial families suggests a connection to algebraic complexity theory, which is often studied in the cs.CC sub-category. The paper also involves combinatorial objects and black-box algorithms, which are relevant to the cs.DS and cs.CG sub-categories. The use of seed length and explicitness criteria suggests a connection to information theory and cryptography, which are often studied in the cs.IT sub-category. Finally, the paper involves hardness-randomness tradeoffs and progress on the VP versus VNP problem, which are relevant to the cs.DM sub-category.
